{"questionId":"33397544","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Mai is standing at the attraction at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math> and wants to walk directly to the attraction at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the distance between <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>use of Pythagoras&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AB</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mn>12</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>4</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>12</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6491</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msqrt><mn>160</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33397544","referenceCode":"24M.2.SL.TZ2.2b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Calculate the distance between A and B.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.1—3d space, volume, angles, midpoints","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.3—Angles of elevation and depression"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
